<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="517" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,599,1058]" pageId="15" pageNumber="517">
The specimen examined here (
<figureCitation box="[558,697,635,662]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–37" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,184,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,170,1938]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 32–37. Figs. 32–33. Montina lobata, dorsal view, scale bar 5.0 mm, 32, female, 33, male. Figs. 34–35. Montina sinuosa, female, 34, dorsal view, scale bar 5.0 mm, 35, abdomen, lateral view, scale bar 2.0 mm. Figs. 36–37. Zelus lewisi, female, dorsal view, 36, scale bar 5.0 mm, 37, head and thorax, scale bar 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3239893/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="517">Figs. 34–35</figureCitation>
) generally agrees well with the short description (
<bibRefCitation author="Lepeletier, A. L. M. &amp; Serville, J. G. A." pageId="15" pageNumber="517" pagination="1 - 832" refId="ref9312" refString="Lepeletier, A. L. M. &amp; Serville, J. G. A. (1825) Histoire naturelle. Entomologie. In: Olivier, G. A., Encyclopedie Methodique. Vol. 10. Agasse, Paris, pp. 1 - 832." type="book chapter" year="1825">Lepeletier &amp; Serville 1825</bibRefCitation>
) and redescription of the species (
<bibRefCitation author="Amyot, C. J. B. &amp; Serville, J. G. A." box="[692,965,671,698]" pageId="15" pageNumber="517" refId="ref8380" refString="Amyot, C. J. B. &amp; Serville, J. G. A. (1843) Histoire naturelle des insects: Hemipteres. Librairie Encyclopedique de Roret. Fain et Thunot, Paris, 681 pp." type="book" year="1843">Amyot &amp; Serville 1843</bibRefCitation>
). However, these authors provided different measurements for this species, without mentioning the sex of their examined specimens. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lepeletier, A. L. M. &amp; Serville, J. G. A." pageId="15" pageNumber="517" pagination="1 - 832" refId="ref9312" refString="Lepeletier, A. L. M. &amp; Serville, J. G. A. (1825) Histoire naturelle. Entomologie. In: Olivier, G. A., Encyclopedie Methodique. Vol. 10. Agasse, Paris, pp. 1 - 832." type="book chapter" year="1825">Lepeletier &amp; Serville (1825)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned the length of 12 to 14 lines (“lig.”) (approximately 
<quantity box="[944,1114,743,770]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.93" metricValueMax="3.16" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="15" pageNumber="517" unit="mm" value="29.3" valueMax="31.6" valueMin="27.0">27 to 31.6 mm</quantity>
; taking into account that the “ligne” in 
<collectingCountry box="[274,350,780,806]" name="France" pageId="15" pageNumber="517">France</collectingCountry>
was equivalent to 
<quantity box="[572,734,779,806]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25552" pageId="15" pageNumber="517" unit="in" value="0.0888">0.0888 inches</quantity>
; 2,2552 mm), and 
<bibRefCitation author="Amyot, C. J. B. &amp; Serville, J. G. A." box="[955,1246,779,806]" pageId="15" pageNumber="517" refId="ref8380" refString="Amyot, C. J. B. &amp; Serville, J. G. A. (1843) Histoire naturelle des insects: Hemipteres. Librairie Encyclopedique de Roret. Fain et Thunot, Paris, 681 pp." type="book" year="1843">Amyot &amp; Serville (1843)</bibRefCitation>
<quantity box="[1257,1339,780,806]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="15" pageNumber="517" unit="mm" value="24.0">24 mm</quantity>
(“Long. 0,024”). The total length of the female from 
<collectingCountry box="[661,754,815,841]" name="Ecuador" pageId="15" pageNumber="517">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[771,853,815,842]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–37" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,184,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,170,1938]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 32–37. Figs. 32–33. Montina lobata, dorsal view, scale bar 5.0 mm, 32, female, 33, male. Figs. 34–35. Montina sinuosa, female, 34, dorsal view, scale bar 5.0 mm, 35, abdomen, lateral view, scale bar 2.0 mm. Figs. 36–37. Zelus lewisi, female, dorsal view, 36, scale bar 5.0 mm, 37, head and thorax, scale bar 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3239893/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="517">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) to the tip of abdomen and hemelytra measured 23 and 
<quantity box="[200,281,852,878]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="15" pageNumber="517" unit="mm" value="27.0">27 mm</quantity>
, respectively, which is in accordance with the measurements recorded by the previous authors for this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
